column1: Will Iraq's parliament elect a new President of the Republic before 6 November 2022?

column6: Woops. Maybe biggest forecasting miss I've yet made

“Anything is possible in Iraq” is not a slogan, and for good reason. The people of Iraq deserve better. Even if a new (hypothetical) push were to begin today, I also don’t think there’s enough time left for the deliberations/process to play out in parliament.
Ok seems like protesters are agitating for a new election. It's hard to see that being parlayed into a consensus presidential appointment
I have a very poor read on the situation, Iraqi Constitutional law, and how this question would resolve in different scenarios, so increasing my uncertainty
Things are not moving in a positive direction, and the time window is getting shorter.

Parliament could be dissolved (https://www.al-monitor.com/originals/2022/08/iraqs-sadr-sets-deadline-dissolve-parliament) which would lead to elections and then the election of a President. Looks highly unlikely all that will occur in less than 3 months.
I don't think I'm right. I don't know that I'm right. But I feel that I am right.

The current crisis has been going on for months now and there is no clear way out. A snap election might help (https://www.wionews.com/world/dissolve-the-parliament-influential-shiite-leader-moqtada-sadr-calls-for-fresh-elections-in-iraq-503371) but there are a few barriers.
